{"lemma": "فارَ", "slug": "فارَ", "root": "ف.#.ر", "root_slug": "ف-_-ر", "root_link": "/words/roots/ف-_-ر", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": true, "lemma_key": "فارَ", "root": "فور", "pos": "V", "occurrence_count": 3}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 1}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n32823", "n33326", "n34790"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%81%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8E"}}, "translations": {"en": "mouse", "fa": "موش", "ur": "چوہا", "tr": "fare", "id": "tikus", "bn": "ইঁদুর", "es": "ratón", "fr": "souris", "de": "Maus", "ru": "мышь", "zh": "老鼠"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to overflow, to gush forth, to boil up"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": null, "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n32823", "headword_ar": "فَاْرٌ", "root": "fA^r", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A kind of animal,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "well known,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K,) [the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "genus mus;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rat;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mouse;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the like"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Lth, S, Msb,) and without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (Msb;) [a coll. gen. n.:] n. un. with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "p", "text_ar": "ة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (Lth, T:) [in the S and O and Msb,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orN", "text_ar": "فَاْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is said to be pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapN", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", but in the last is added, like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamorapN", "text_ar": "تَمْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tamorN", "text_ar": "تَمْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", showing that by pl. is meant coll. gen. n.:] the pl. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fA^r", "text_ar": "فار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Lth, T, M, K,) or of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fA^rp", "text_ar": "فارة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, Msb,) is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiy^oraAnN", "text_ar": "فِيْرَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Lth, T, M, O, K, Msb) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiy^irapN", "text_ar": "فِيِرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M, K:) accord. to IAar, (T, TA,) ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw^arN", "text_ar": "فُوَرٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SuradN", "text_ar": "صُرَدٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (O, K, TA,) is applied to the male: (T, O, K, TA:) but this last word occurs in the phrase"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfaA^or Alfuw^ar", "text_ar": "الفَاْر الفُوَر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [in which"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfA^r", "text_ar": "الفار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is evidently used in a sense mentioned below, namely, “ the muscles, ” as is indicated in the T and O,] and, accord. to some, ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alfuw^ar", "text_ar": "الفُوَر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is a corroborative epithet, for they say that] this phrase is like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "layolN laAy^ilN", "text_ar": "لَيْلٌ لَايِلٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yawomN A^ayowamu", "text_ar": "يَوْمٌ اَيْوَمُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (O:)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapN", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied [accord. to some] to the female; (M;) or [more correctly] to the male and the female, (M, K,) like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HamaAmapN", "text_ar": "حَمَامَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to the male and the female of the [genus]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "HamaAm", "text_ar": "حَمَام"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Musk:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K:) this is sometimes called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orN", "text_ar": "فَاْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because it is from the [animal, or from a kind of animal, called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^or", "text_ar": "فَاْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", as some say. (M.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapu Almisoki", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةُ المِسْكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The bag, follicle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "vesicle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAfijap", "text_ar": "نَافِجَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", S, M, O, K, or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "naAfiqap", "text_ar": "نَافِقَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", T,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of musk:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, O, K:) and is also without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M, Msb;) or it should correctly be mentioned in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwr", "text_ar": "فور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [as being called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faArapN", "text_ar": "فَارَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] because of the spreading ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawaraAn", "text_ar": "فَوَرَان"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") of its odour: or it may be with"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "because it has the appearance, or form, of the [animal called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orap", "text_ar": "فَاْرَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (O, K.) It was said to an Arab of the desert"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atahomizu AlfaA^orapa", "text_ar": "اَتَهْمِزُ الفَاْرَةَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K, TA, in the CK"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^atuhomazu AlfaA^oru", "text_ar": "اَتُهْمَزُ الفَاْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",) [meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Dost thou pronounce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fArp", "text_ar": "فارة"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "with hemz?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "], and he replied, [understanding the animal so called to be meant,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Alhir~apu tahomizuhaA", "text_ar": "الهِرَّةُ تَهْمِزُهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) meaning, ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The cat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bites it."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  [Hence, app., by a synecdoche,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapu Almisoki", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةُ المِسْكِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The mush-animal,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Tibet-musk; moschus moschiferus:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] El-Jáhidh says, I asked a perfumer, of [the sect of] the Moatezileh, respecting [the animal called]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fA^rp Almsk", "text_ar": "فارة المسك"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", and he said,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it is not a mouse,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fA^rp", "text_ar": "فارة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ",)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "but is more like a young gazelle: it is found in the region of Tubbat"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Tibet"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "];"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and is hunted; and the man who catches it binds tightly its navel,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or rather"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "its umbilical follicle,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which being pendent, the blood collects in it; then it is slaughtered; and when it is quiet, he cuts out the bound navel, and buries it in barley"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$Eyr", "text_ar": "شعير"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ")"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "until the congealed blood becomes converted into strong-scented musk."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b5-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapu AlA_ibili", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةُ الاـِبِلِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The sweet odour of the camels,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "likened to that of the vesicle of musk,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "which diffuses itself from them when they have pastured upon the herbs and their blossoms,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O,) or, as some say,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "upon the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "plant called"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "xuzaAmaY", "text_ar": "خُزَامَى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.], (O,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "and then drunk, and returned from the water, with their skins moist:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O:) so says Yaakoob. (S.) Thus in a verse cited voce"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "*afirN", "text_ar": "ذَفِرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (S, O. [Therefore"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapN *aforaA='u", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةٌ ذَفْرَا=ءُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "should there be rendered"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A pungent sweet odour like that of a vesicle of musk."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "But see"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faArap", "text_ar": "فَارَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwr", "text_ar": "فور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfaA^oru", "text_ar": "الفَاْرُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifies also (assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The muscles:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, O:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^oru Almatoni", "text_ar": "فَاْرُ المَتْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(assumed tropical:)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the flesh on either side of the back-bone;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yaraAbiyEu Almatoni", "text_ar": "يَرَابِيعُ المَتْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ". (T. [See also"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlfaAru", "text_ar": "الفَارُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fwr", "text_ar": "فور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".])       -A3-  And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A species of trees;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "with and without"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "'", "text_ar": "ء"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faA^orapN", "text_ar": "فَاْرَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as its n. un.]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a tree"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of that species"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (K.)       -A4-  Also"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A certain well-known measure,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "quantity, of wheat:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in this sense an adventitious word. (O.)"}], "source_refs": ["M", "K", "Lth", "S", "Msb", "T", "O", "TA"]}, {"entry_id": "n33326", "headword_ar": "فَارٌّ", "root": "fr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": "(S, M) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "far~N", "text_ar": "فَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, O, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faruwrN", "text_ar": "فَرُورٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faruwrapN", "text_ar": "فَرُورَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "far~aArN", "text_ar": "فَرَّارٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, O, K) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "furarapN", "text_ar": "فُرَرَةٌ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K) are epithets from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "far~a", "text_ar": "فَرَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "signifying as expl. in the first sentence of this art.: (S, T, M, O, K:) [the first and second meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Fleeing;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "turning away"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "aside, to elude, and fleeing:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "the third, fifth, and sixth,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fleeing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "much:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and the fourth,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fleeing,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "very much:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] but ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "far~N", "text_ar": "فَرٌّ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is applied to one and to two and to more, and to a female; (S, O;) it has no dual nor pl. [nor fem. form]; (T;) the sing. [and dual] and pl. [and mase. and fem.] are alike; (M;) as it is an inf. n. used as an epithet; (M, O;) and it may be a"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2357}, {"kind": "text", "text": "pl. [or rather a quasi-pl. n.] of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faAr~N", "text_ar": "فَارٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, M, O,) like as"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "rakobN", "text_ar": "رَكْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "is of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "raAkibN", "text_ar": "رَاكِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O,) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaHobN", "text_ar": "صَحْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "SaAHibN", "text_ar": "صَاحِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K, *) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$arobN", "text_ar": "شَرْبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "$aAribN", "text_ar": "شَارِبٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": (M:) it is related in the trad. respecting the Flight that Surákah Ibn-Málik, when he saw the Prophet and Aboo-Bekr fleeing to El-Medeeneh, and they passed by him, said,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "h`*aAni far~N quray$K A^afalaA A^arud~u EalaY", "text_ar": "هٰذَانِ فَرٌّ قُرَيشٍ اَفَلَا اَرُدُّ عَلَى"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qurayo$K far~ahaA", "text_ar": "قُرَيْشٍ فَرَّهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (T, * S, * O, * TA,) meaning ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "These two are"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "two"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "fugitives"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of Kureysh: shall I not turn back to Kureysh their fugitives?"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (A 'Obeyd, T, TA.)"}], "source_refs": ["S", "M", "T", "O", "K"]}, {"entry_id": "n34790", "headword_ar": "فَارَ", "root": "fwr", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (M, Msb, K,) aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "yafuwru", "text_ar": "يَفُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said of water; (Msb;) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faArato", "text_ar": "فَارَتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "tafuwru", "text_ar": "تَفُورُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", said of a"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qidor", "text_ar": "قِدْر"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2457}, {"kind": "text", "text": "cooking-pot]; (T, S;) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "faworN", "text_ar": "فَوْرٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fawaraAnN", "text_ar": "فَوَرَانٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Msb, K) [the latter of which is the more common] and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuw^uwrN", "text_ar": "فُوُورٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(M, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fuwaArN", "text_ar": "فُوَارٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (M, TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It boiled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "estuated."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, M, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-  ["}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fAr", "text_ar": "فار"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said of a liquor,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It fermented."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(See"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "nabiy*N", "text_ar": "نَبِيذٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b3-  Said of blood, and of wine,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It flushed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "mantled,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the cheeks or head.] ―         -b4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fArt nafosuhu", "text_ar": "فارت نَفْسُهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His soul"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "stomach"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "heaved;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "became agitated by a tendency to vomit; i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vArt", "text_ar": "ثارت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.]. (T in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vwr", "text_ar": "ثور"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ".) ―         -b5-  ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fAr faAy^iruhu", "text_ar": "فار فَايِرُهُ", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "i. q."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "vAr vaAy^iruhu", "text_ar": "ثار ثَايِرُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, K)"}, {"ki